I believe that the idea of the project is very good, however, it does not aligns well or effectively addresses the challenge. The brief of the challenge clearly states that this is a exclusive space for students to put their ideas and to be seen by the engineers in the Cardano Ecosystem. The KPI's provided by the proposer make sense with the project, but they do not match the ones indicated in the challenge. 
I agree that the project presented a solution to a existing problem in Brazil, addressing even the language barrier, and the local impact is significant to the students interested in Cardano and blockchain technology, which would add a high value to the Cardano Ecosystem with more and more people interested in the subject. But I see some problems with the proposal:
- The proposer is not a student;
- Once the project scales, by the construction of a blockchain and Cardano hub, how would these courses be offered to all Brazilian community, since some of the classes should be taken personally? 
- One important KPI that the proposer should take into consideration is the number of submitted proposals by students that took the course (which would be a great measurement of success as well);
For these reasons, I deliberate the assessment above.
